Tusk Says Poland May Bolster Zloty, Doesn’t Plan to ‘Constantly Intervene’

-- B y   D a v i d   M c Q u a i d
-- 
2011-09-23T08:57:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/tusk-says-poland-may-bolster-zloty-doesn-t-plan-to-constantly-intervene-.html
While  Poland  will use the
instruments at its disposal to help stabilize the zloty, “the
point is not to constantly intervene” on financial markets over
which local policy makers have little control, Prime Minister
Donald Tusk told reporters today at a campaign appearance in
Uraz, Poland.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David McQuaid at 
 dmcquaid1@bloomberg.net  